      "writtenOn": "2015-08-31T09:36:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For now it is not possible, following query includes one association not mapped in hibernate model therefore using criteria here is not feasible at the moment. We would like to have it instead raw-string based queries but having that would lead to another major schema change where adding a column would be trifle but writing a migration, well...it wouldn\u0027t be so obvious. The table/entity we are talking about is metric_dimension. This particular one has no primary key while it has unique index for two of its columns. That is not a problem in hibernate model, because we can easily understand unique key as primary key and there is no difference. What is important is that based on queries in project metric_dimension is being associated with metric_definiton_dimension. Now, in order to understand it a proper entity association we would have to alter either metric_definition_dimension by adding new column \u003e metric_definiton_set_name \u003c correlated with metric_definition_set_id and thus creating composite foreign key pointing at metric_dimension (where unique key would be changed to primary key). Alternative would be adding primary key to metric_dimension and calculating it in a way that would be agnostic to any ORM tool we can think of, meaning to say leave that job to database itself. But again that would mean going into trigger to do that. In brief all that comes down to schema modification to make it mappable in ORM tool Hibernate is.",
